  "instructions": [
    "Heat oil in a large Dutch oven over medium-high heat.",
    "Add the chopped onion and cook until translucent, about 5 minutes.",
    "Add the minced garlic and grated ginger, cook for 1 minute.",
    "Add the turkey neck and cook until browned, about 5 minutes.",
    "Add the berbere spice, turmeric, cumin, black pepper, and salt. Cook for 1 minute.",
    "Add 4 cups of water to the pot and bring to a boil.",
    "Reduce the heat to low and simmer, covered, for 30 minutes.",
    "Preheat the oven to 425°F (220°C).",
    "Carefully place the hot stone bowl on a baking sheet.",
    "Transfer the turkey neck and sauce to the stone bowl.",
    "Bake in the oven for 10-15 minutes, or until the top is crispy.",
    "Finish with clarified butter and garnish with torn ketewa.",
    "Ensure poultry is cooked to an internal temperature of 74°C / 165°F (juices run clear, no pink remaining) before serving."
  ],
